[Clinical signs of distemper include dyspnea, ataxia, clonic convulsions,
spasms of the hind legs, ascending paralysis, progressive blindness, loss
of appetite, emaciation, diarrhea, and coma. There is an excellent
discussion of the disease in raccoons in the archived file "Canine
distemper, raccoons - USA (Minnesota) (02)" 19990803.1330, which is cited
above. ­ Mod.TG
